  To get it running you need:

  1. PostgreSQL — createdb stockinvest
  2. Local LLM — either Ollama (`ollama pull qwen3-30b-a3b`) or llama.cpp with a GGUF model path
  3. API keys — copy .env.example to .env and fill in OPENAI_API_KEY + DATABASE_URL
  4. Install deps — pip install -r requirements.txt
     - Optional llama.cpp path — pip install -r requirements-llamacpp.txt
     - For NVIDIA/CUDA llama.cpp builds, use CMAKE_ARGS="-DGGML_CUDA=on" FORCE_CMAKE=1 pip install --force-reinstall --no-cache-dir --no-binary llama-cpp-python -r requirements-llamacpp.txt
  5. Test run — python scheduler.py --now (runs pipeline immediately)
  6. Dashboard — uvicorn main:app --reload then open http://localhost:8000

  Architecture flow:

  Data (YFinance) → 4 Analysts (local model) → Bull+Bear Debate (cloud OpenAI)
