⏺ Here's the full setup for PostgreSQL on macOS:

  1. Install PostgreSQL (if not already installed):

  brew install postgresql@17

  2. Start the service:

  brew services start postgresql@17

  3. Create the database:

  createdb stockinvest

  4. Verify it works:

  psql stockinvest -c "SELECT 1;"

  5. Update your .env:

  DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/stockinvest

  The default config uses your macOS username with no password for local connections, which is how Homebrew PostgreSQL ships. The app will auto-create all tables on first startup via
   init_db().
